.TH COREDOC 1 "July 2026" "coredoc 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
coredoc \- modular Linux diagnostics and first-aid TUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B coredoc
[B--jsonR] [B--doctorR DOCTOR] [B--appR NAME] [B--support-bundleR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
coredoc launches a Textual terminal interface for Linux diagnostics. It can also print structured JSON for individual diagnostic modules.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Print JSON instead of launching the TUI.
.TP
.B --doctor DOCTOR
Run one doctor: audio, wayland, sleep, clean, logs, hardware, permissions.
.TP
.B --app NAME
Application name for the clean doctor.
.TP
.B --support-bundle
Write a sanitised support bundle tarball.
